❯ We're not building an app. I work as an independent contractor on behalf of large insurance companies who send me claims for   
  independent analysis. Most jobs do not require an onsite visit (desk jobs), so I receive the claims detail from an insurance   
  adjuster, then I get to work calling the claimant, other parties involved, third-party vendors and repair/services providers   
  and contractors. I document all of these calls and my investigative ("review") work in a zip file for each claim I'm asked to  
  review, and ultimately, I provide the insurer with my own assessment of the total costs they should reasonably be paying out   
  on the claim. I would like to train you to write my finalized reports to the clients, which are fairly standardized but have   
  some variation with each claim. But, I need you to act as the Lead Insurance Claims Review Orchestrator to create              
  documentation and build a system that allows you to spawn subagents, each with clean context windows, to review all the        
  documentation I've pulled together and actually write the final report for my review, pushing its draft to github with         
  appropriate summary documentation.                                                                                             

⏺ That's a much clearer picture - thank you. This is essentially an orchestrated Claude Code workflow system, not an application. You
   want:

  1. Documentation & templates that teach Claude how to write your reports
  2. An orchestration structure so Claude can spawn subagents to process claim zip files
  3. A pipeline that goes from raw claim docs → subagent review → drafted report → GitHub PR

