⏺ Excellent - I now have a complete end-to-end understanding of the Main Street Tacos bundle. Let me document the key mapping
  patterns I've extracted while waiting for the background agents.

  What I've learned from this deep dive:

  Raw Notes → Final Report mapping:
  - Casual call notes ("caught on fire, wire melted") get cleaned into professional-but-simple language
  - The vendor fraud investigation (fake Ice Berg invoice) was documented faithfully in the report
  - Multiple vendor proposals get separate cost analysis sections

  Spreadsheet structure:
  - CLAIM PRESENTED vs LSG RESEARCHED RCV columns
  - ACV = RCV * (1 - age/useful_life), capped at 75% max depreciation
  - Labor, permits, disposal are NOT depreciated (N/A)
  - Lump sums get broken down with vendor help

  Invoice Summary:
  - Categories: File Review & Client Contact, Insured, Vendors, Research & Technical Analysis, Report & Spreadsheet
  - Rate: $175/hr, rounded to nearest 0.25hr increments

  Let me check on the background agents' progress.

